= \n Biography\n


Dr. Wen Wu is an associate researcher at the Frontier Research Center at Peng Cheng Laboratory, Shenzhen, Guangdong, China. He received the B.E. degree in Information Engineering from South China University of Technology, Guangzhou, China, and the M.E. degree in Electrical Engineering from the University of Science and Technology of China, Hefei, China, in 2012 and 2015, respectively. He received his Ph.D. in Electrical and Computer Engineering from the University of Waterloo, Waterloo, ON, Canada, in 2019, and then worked as a Postdoctoral Research Fellow in the Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering, University of Waterloo, before joining the Peng Cheng Laboratory. Dr. Wu’s research focuses on 6G networks, network virtualization, network intelligence, and networking for AI. \n

\n
Dr. Wu serves\/served on TPCs and organizing committees for a number of ACM\/IEEE conferences, including the Workshop TPC Co-Chair for IEEE INFOCOM 2022, the Track Chair of EAI CollaborateCom 2021, and the Workshop Co-Chair for IEEE IPCCC 2021 and IEEE HPCC 2021. Dr. Wu serves\/served on the editorial board for Hindawi Wireless Communications and Mobile Computing, China Communications, Frontiers in Internet of Things, and Springer Peer-to-Peer Networking and Applications. Dr. Wu serves\/served as a Technical Program Committee (TPC) Member for several international conferences, including the FL-IJCAI’22, IEEE ICC’22, IEEE Globecom’22, IEEE VTC’22, and IEEE WCSP’19. He is a Senior Member of IEEE and China Institute of Communications (CIC). Dr. Wu serves as the Distinguished Researcher (Level-C) in the Peng Cheng Laboratory.\n
